8 POLICY COMMITTEE RECOMMENDATION
9 An Act relating to State Question 780 data; amending
57 O.S. 2021, Section 632, as amended by Section 2,
10 Chapter 201, O.S.L. 2023, and as renumbered by
Section 6, Chapter 201, O.S.L. 2023 (43A O.S. Supp.
11 2025, Section 2-312.2), which relates to calculation
of savings and averted costs from implementation of
12 the Oklahoma Smart Justice Reform Act; requiring the
Department of Corrections to provide certain data to
13 the Legislative Office of Fiscal Transparency;
requiring the Administrator of the Courts to provide
14 certain data to the Legislative Office of Fiscal
Transparency; and providing an effective date.
15
16
17
18 BE IT ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
19 SECTION 1. AMENDATORY 57 O.S. 2021, Section 632, as
20 amended by Section 2, Chapter 201, O.S.L. 2023, and as renumbered by
21 Section 6, Chapter 201, O.S.L. 2023 (43A O.S. Supp. 2025, Section 2-
22 312.2), is amended to read as follows:
23 Section 2-312.2. No later than July 31 of each year, the
24 Department of Corrections shall provide the Legislative Office of
Req. No. 16546 Page 1

1 Fisc al Transparency with data for the prior fiscal year ending June
2 30, reflecting the number of unique offenders and days served by
3 each offender, upon completion of the corresponding sentence, for
4 those convicted only of crimes modified by State Question 780. No
5 later than July 31 of each year, the Administrator of the Courts
6 shall provide the Legislative Office of Fiscal Transparency with
7 data necessary to calculate the annual savings and averted costs,
8 including the number of persons convicted only of crimes modified by
9 State Question 780 and the number of days sentenced for such crimes.
10 For purposes of this section, crimes modified by State Question 780
11 shall include only those crimes that were previously felonies that
12 are now misdemeanors and crimes that fall between the former dollar
13 threshold and current dollar threshold for crimes whose severity is
14 determined by a dollar threshold. No later than thirty (30) days
15 after being provided with the data from both the Department of
16 Corrections and the Administrator of the Courts, the Legislative
17 Office of Fiscal Transparency shall calculate the annual savings and
18 averted costs from the prior fiscal year that accrued to the state
19 due to the reduction of the number and length of incarcerations
20 attributed to the implementation of the Oklahoma Smart Justice
21 Reform Act. In making the calculation required by this section, the
22 Legislative Office of Fiscal Transparency shall use actual data or
23 best available estimates where actual data is not available. The
24
Req. No. 16546 Page 2

1 calc ulation shall be final and shall not be adjusted for any
2 subsequent changes in the underlying data.
3 SECTION 2. This act shall become effective November 1, 2026.
